ssage","correct":false,"explanation":"Routing is automatic and invisible. The gateway figures it out from the config bindings."}],"concept":"Route Resolution","difficulty":"easy"},{"type":"river","trigger":"after_stop","triggerStop":3,"title":"The Session State River","text":"You've reached the boundary between stateless request handling and persistent memory. Your assistant needs to remember last week's conversation across a restart. How do you cross?","choices":[{"text":"Store sessions as JSON files on disk, loaded on demand per key","correct":true,"explanation":"Each session is a JSON file at a predictable path. No database needed. The file system IS the persistence layer."},{"text":"Keep all sessions in memory with a Redis cache","correct":false,"explanation":"In-memory state is lost on restart. Redis adds an external dependency. OpenClaw is local-first."},{"text":"Store history in the AI model's context and let it remember","correct":false,"explanation":"Context windows are limited and expensive. The persistence layer is separate from inference."}],"concept":"Session Persistence","difficulty":"medium"},{"type":"misfortune","trigger":"after_stop","triggerStop":5,"title":"Runaway Process!","text":"The AI agent ran a shell command that's an infinite loop consuming 100% CPU. Your gateway is grinding to a halt!","choices":[{"text":"Tool execution needs timeouts and session security policies should gate commands","correct":true,"explanation":"Bash tools have a two-minute timeout, and security policies control what's allowed. The gateway is the security boundary."},{"text":"The agent should be smarter and never request dangerous commands","correct":false,"explanation":"Never rely on the AI as the security boundary. Defense in depth means the gateway enforces limits."},{"text":"Run all tools in the agent's process so only it crashes","correct":false,"explanation":"Tools run on the gateway because they need local machine access. The separation is a feature."}],"concept":"Gateway Control Plane","difficulty":"medium"},{"type":"river","trigger":"after_stop","triggerStop":5,"title":"The RPC River","text":"The deepest river — the boundary between gateway and agent runtime. The agent needs a browser screenshot but runs in a different process. How?","choices":[{"text":"JSON-RPC over WebSocket: agent requests, gateway executes locally","correct":true,"explanation":"The agent streams tool_use blocks, the gateway intercepts and executes. The agent could run remotely."},{"text":"The agent directly imports and calls the browser module","correct":false,"explanation":"Separate processes can't call each other's code. The RPC boundary IS the security model."},{"text":"The agent writes commands to a shared file the gateway watches","correct":false,"explanation":"File watching is slow and unreliable. WebSocket RPC gives real-time bidirectional streaming."}],"concept":"Gateway Control Plane","difficulty":"hard"},{"type":"fortune","trigger":"after_stop","triggerStop":6,"title":"Spring of Clean Architecture","text":"Your understanding of the control plane is solid! Friendly contributors join your camp and share plugin templates.","choices":[],"concept":"Channel Plugins","difficulty":"easy"},{"type":"weather","trigger":"after_stop","triggerStop":6,"title":"Message Chunking Fog","text":"Dense fog. Your assistant wrote 3000 words but WhatsApp only allows 4096 characters. The user sees a truncated response. What went wrong?","choices":[{"text":"The formatter should chunk messages based on each channel's limit","correct":true,"explanation":"WhatsApp: 4096, Discord: 2000, Slack: 40000. The delivery layer splits into properly-sized chunks."},{"text":"Tell the AI to always write short responses","correct":false,"explanation":"You can't enforce output length on LLMs. The delivery layer handles formatting."},{"text":"Switch to a channel with no message limits","correct":false,"explanation":"Multi-channel means meeting users where they are. Every channel must work correctly."}],"concept":"Channel Plugins","difficulty":"easy"}],"partyMembers":[{"name":"Gateway Control Plane","icon":"gateway","maxHealth":3},{"name":"Channel Plugins","icon":"channel","maxHealth":3},{"name":"Route Resolution","icon":"route","maxHealth":3},{"name":"Session Persistence","icon":"session","maxHealth":3}],"deathMessages":["You have died of unhandled WebSocket disconnections.","You have died of missing default routes.","You have drowned in the RPC River.","You have died of session bloat.","You have died of a runaway bash command.","You have died of unhandled plugin exceptions.","You have died of API rate limits.","You have died of dependency conflicts.","You have died of expired sessions.","You have died of Discord snowflake avalanche.","You have died of invalid routing config."]};
